Algorithm: 

The new algorithm assigns scores to each bin based on a modified version of the previous algorithm. The modified algorithm takes the difference between the bin capacity and the item size, raises it to the power of the logarithm of the bin capacity divided by the item size, multiplies it by the square root of the bin capacity divided by the item size, adds 1 to it, and finally takes the reciprocal of this value. The score of each bin is then normalized by dividing it by the maximum score across all bins.

Python Implementation:

```
code:
import numpy as np

def score(item: int, bins: np.ndarray) -> np.ndarray:
    # Calculate the scores for the bins
    scores = (1 / (((bins - item)**(np.log(bins / item))) * np.sqrt(bins / item) + 1))
    
    # Normalize the scores by dividing by the maximum score
    max_score = np.max(scores)
    scores = scores / max_score
    
    return scores
